track_notes:
Park at Degollada de la Aldea (also a Bus Stop) and follow the marked trail. It follows below the cliff until you can ascend and then turns back on a spectacular track. Great views of Teide included!  

It is a long but technically not difficult hike with great vistas. The route is exposed to the South-West. If you start early enough you should get some shade during ascend.

There is a trig-point at the summit and also some pine trees to tie a mast to. 

No water along the route, carry plenty!

This is the route I have chosen for descend. Combined with the South ascend you circle the whole mountain.

It is hardly marked, but easy to find, although a bit overgrown in the section north of the summit. Long pants recommended or you might get a lot of scratches!
